Notes.Title: Components of Process Control Block
Notes.Content: The Process Control Block (PCB) includes several key components that are essential for process management in an operating system. These components are: 1. Process state, 2. Program counter, 3. CPU registers, 4. CPU-scheduling information, 5. Memory-management information, 6. Accounting information, and 7. I/O status information.

Notes.Title: Exclusions from PCB
Notes.Content: The items that are not included in the Process Control Block are: (A) CPU-scheduling, (B) Kernel device driver, (C) I/O-Device Queries, (D) Memory-management info, (E) Object Ref, (F) CPU registers, and (G) Bitmap. The correct exclusions are: (B) Kernel device driver, (C) I/O-Device Queries, (D) Memory-management info, (E) Object Ref, (G) Bitmap.
Notes.Wrong_Content: The items that are not included in the Process Control Block are: (A) CPU-scheduling, (B) Kernel device driver, (C) I/O-Device Queries, (D) Memory-management info, (E) Object Ref, (F) CPU registers, and (G) Bitmap. The correct exclusions are B and E.
